NT: WooCommerce 2 is no longer supported! If you are still using Woo 2.x, do NOT upgrade!</h5>\n</blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li>COMPATIBILITY:\n<ul>\n<li>WordPress 4.8</li>\n<li>WooCommerce 3.1.0</li>\n<li>WooCommerce Composite Products 3.10.1</li>\n<li>WooCommerce Dynamic Pricing 3.0.9</li>\n<li>WooCommerce Subscriptions 2.2.8</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>FIXED:\n<ul>\n<li>Filter the output of <code>get_description()</code>.</li>\n<li>Correctly display the Composite Product properties under WC 3.1.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<ul>\n<li>Subscribe to the <a href="https://wpglobus.com/product/woocommerce-wpglobus/">WPGlobus extension for WooCommerce</a> upgrades and support!</li>\n<li>Read the <a href="https://wpglobus.com/extensions/woocommerce-wpglobus/woocommerce-wpglobus-changelog/">complete history of changes</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://wpglobus.com/plugin-updates/woocommerce-wpglobus-update-%f0%9f%8c%90/">WPGlobus for WooCommerce 3.1.0</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://wpglobus.com">WPGlobus</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:33:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"WPGlobus Plus 1.1.33";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:57:"https://wpglobus.com/plugin-updates/wpglobus-plus-update/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 23 Jun 2017 00:00:39 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"Plugin Updates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"https://wpglobus.com/?p=11193";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:531:"<p>In this version: We added a new module, "Taxonomies". It will allow URL translation at the level of category name, tag name and any custom taxonomy. The module will not be enabled by default until we finish the extensive testing and QA. If you\'d like to check it out, please contact us for the instructions. &#91;...&#93;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://wpglobus.com/plugin-updates/wpglobus-plus-update/">WPGlobus Plus 1.1.33</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://wpglobus.com">WPGlobus</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"Gregory Karpinsky";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2504:"<h3>In this version:</h3>\n<p>We added a new module, &#8220;Taxonomies&#8221;. It will allow URL translation at the level of category name, tag name and any custom taxonomy.</p>\n<p><strong>The module will not be enabled by default until we finish the extensive testing and QA. If you&#8217;d like to check it out, please contact us for the instructions.</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Changes made in the previous releases:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>There were no critical issues fixed, mostly cosmetics, and things that could cause some confusion.</li>\n<li>Specifically, the <code>TinyMCE</code> module was adding the language switching buttons to the places where they were useless: in the posts edited by the Avada&#8217;s Fusion Builder or by the WPBakery&#8217;s Visual Composer. We&#8217;ve fixed that in the release 1.1.32.</li>\n<li>Other changes included code documenting and formatting.</li>\n<li>To avoid the common confusion that WPGlobus Plus is a &#8220;PRO&#8221; version of WPGlobus, we now display a message in the admin area that the main plugin, WPGlobus, should not be deactivated. WPGlobus Plus is not a replacement!</li>\n<li>The upcoming release of WPGlobus will offer an automatic redirect to the language, specified in the visitor&#8217;s browser settings. To support it in WPGlobus Plus, we&#8217;ve added a special filter. This filter prevents redirection if the target language is marked as &#8220;draft&#8221; in the module &#8220;Publish&#8221;.</li>\n<li>In our tests, we saw a case when the post_meta table was corrupted and the values of language status were invalid. Under PHP7 this caused a fatal error. So, while this should never happen under normal operation, we&#8217;ve added an additional validation code.</li>\n<li>Some internal changes include:\n<ul>\n<li>removed the old updater code.</li>\n<li>code cleanup and formatting.</li>\n<li>fixing a spelling error in comments.</li>\n<li>Upgrade to Node v.8; use <code>exec:zip</code> instead of the faulty <code>contrib-compress</code> in Grunt.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<ul>\n<li>Get more information about the <a href="https://wpglobus.com/product/wpglobus-plus/">WPGlobus Plus multilingual extension</a>.</li>\n<li>View the complete <a href="https://wpglobus.com/extensions/wpglobus-plus/changelog/">changelog</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://wpglobus.com/plugin-updates/wpglobus-plus-update/">WPGlobus Plus 1.1.33</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://wpglobus.com">WPGlobus</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:33:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:55:"Automatic First-time Redirect Based on Browser Language";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:90:"https://wpglobus.com/news-archive/automatic-first-time-redirect-based-on-browser-language/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 08 Jun 2017 19:15:16 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"https://wpglobus.com/?p=12128";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:630:"<p>Starting from the version 1.8.0, WPGlobus lets you redirect the first-time visitors to their browser language. This feature is not enabled by default. To turn it on, go to WPGlobus->Redirect page in the admin area. How the Redirect Works All browsers allow the users setting their language preference. By default, it\'s the language set on &#91;...&#93;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://wpglobus.com/news-archive/automatic-first-time-redirect-based-on-browser-language/">Automatic First-time Redirect Based on Browser Language</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://wpglobus.com">WPGlobus</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"Gregory Karpinsky";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3443:"<p><strong>Starting from the version 1.8.0, WPGlobus lets you redirect the first-time visitors to their browser language.</strong></p>\n<p>This feature is not enabled by default. To turn it on, go to WPGlobus->Redirect page in the admin area.</p>\n<p><img class="size-full wp-image-12130 alignnone" src="https://wpglobus.com/app/uploads/2017/06/wpglobus-auto-redirect.png" alt="WPGlobus browser language auto-redirect" width="1024" height="460" srcset="https://wpglobus.com/app/uploads/2017/06/wpglobus-auto-redirect-120x54.png 120w, https://wpglobus.com/app/uploads/2017/06/wpglobus-auto-redirect-300x135.png 300w, https://wpglobus.com/app/uploads/2017/06/wpglobus-auto-redirect-500x225.png 500w, https://wpglobus.com/app/uploads/2017/06/wpglobus-auto-redirect-700x314.png 700w, https://wpglobus.com/app/uploads/2017/06/wpglobus-auto-redirect-768x345.png 768w, https://wpglobus.com/app/uploads/2017/06/wpglobus-auto-redirect.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></p>\n<h2>How the Redirect Works</h2>\n<p>All browsers allow the users setting their language preference. By default, it&#8217;s the language set on your computer or mobile device. It is possible to set your browser to accept content in multiple languages, in order of priority. For example, in Quebec, you can set the preference as Canadian French (fr_CA), if not available then any type of French, and finally any type of English.</p>\n<p>The browser then sends to the web server a special HTTP header, which might look like:</p>\n<p><code>Accept-Language: fr-ca, fr;q=0.8, en;q=0.7</code></p>\n<p>WPGlobus receives the header and reads the first two letters (<code>fr</code> in the above example). Then it checks if the requested page is available in the <code>fr</code> language code and redirects the visitor to that page. Then, it stores a cookie telling that the first-time redirect is done and never attempts to redirect again unless the cookie is cleaned.</p>\n<h2>Will the browser language redirect affect the site indexing by Google and other crawlers?</h2>\n<p>According to the &#8220;<a href="https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/6144055?hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Locale-aware crawling by Googlebot</a>&#8221; article, Google is aware of the technique:</p>\n<blockquote><p>If your site alters its content based on any Accept-Language field set by browsers’ HTTP headers, Googlebot uses a variety of signals to try to crawl your content using different Accept-Language HTTP headers. This means Google is more likely to discover, index, and rank your content in the different languages your site supports.</p></blockquote>\n<p>Google will also know that several versions of the same page exist because WPGlobus puts the &#8220;hreflang&#8221; annotations to each page header.</p>\n<p>So, we strongly believe that the first-time redirect will not affect the site indexing. As with all SEO subjects, things are constantly changes, so please keep verifying the indexing status of your site with the Webmaster tools.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><em>Questions? Please <a href="https://wpglobus.com/pg/contact-us/">contact us</a> and we&#8217;ll be glad to assist.</em></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://wpglobus.com/news-archive/automatic-first-time-redirect-based-on-browser-language/">Automatic First-time Redirect Based on Browser Language</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://wpglobus.com">WPGlobus</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:1:{s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:4:"href";s:26:"https://wpglobus.com/feed/";s:3:"rel";s:4:"self";s:4:"type";s:19:"application/rss+xml";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syn